<h1>About this Sinatra app</h1>

<p>This is <code>app/hello.rb</code>, a real
   <a href="https://github.com/sinatra/sinatra">sinatra/sinatra</a> 4.x
   application running on Cloudflare Workers. Phase 13 moved off the
   old <code>janbiedermann/sinatra</code> fork; we now track upstream
   Sinatra with Opal-specific patches in-repo. The file would run
   unchanged on any Rack server; the Cloudflare adapter lives entirely
   in <code>lib/cloudflare_workers.rb</code> and does not leak through.</p>

<h2>Architecture</h2>
<img src="/architecture.svg" alt="homurabi architecture diagram" style="width:100%; max-width:800px; margin:1em 0;">

<h2>How the pieces fit</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Sinatra DSL &rarr; Opal compiler &rarr; a ~1.07 MiB gzipped ESM bundle
      (~1068 KiB after Phase 15-Pre; previously ~580 KiB / ~1.3 MiB in older snapshots)</li>
  <li>ERB templates in <code>views/*.erb</code> &rarr; precompiled by
      <code>bin/compile-erb</code> &rarr; <code>HomurabiTemplates</code>
      registry &rarr; <code>erb :name</code> helper</li>
  <li>Cloudflare bindings cover D1, KV, R2, Workers AI, Queues, Durable Objects,
      and the Workers Cache API. Ruby reaches D1/KV/R2/AI/queues/DO namespaces via
      <code>env['cloudflare.DB']</code>, <code>env['cloudflare.KV']</code>,
      <code>env['cloudflare.BUCKET']</code>, <code>env['cloudflare.AI']</code>,
      <code>env['cloudflare.QUEUE_*']</code>, and <code>env['cloudflare.DO_*']</code>;
      cache reads/writes use the <code>Cloudflare::Cache</code> wrapper over
      <code>caches.default</code> / <code>caches.open</code>.</li>
  <li>Phase 12.5 added Fiber-transparent <code>await</code>; most routes no
      longer hand-roll <code>.__await__</code>. Edge cases that still need
      explicit async can use <code># await: true</code> as before.</li>
</ul>

<h2>Posts, login, and chat (Phase 14)</h2>
<p>The app now includes <a href="/posts"><code>/posts</code></a> backed by a
   D1 <code>posts</code> table, <a href="/login"><code>/login</code></a> for
   the session / OAuth-style login flow, and <a href="/chat"><code>/chat</code></a>
   for the streaming assistant UI. Together they exercise bindings, templates,
   and async paths beyond the original hello-world surface.</p>

<h2>Recent improvements (Phase 15-Pre)</h2>
<p>Deploy reliability improved: <code>wrangler deploy</code> succeeded three
   times in a row on the tightening bundle. The worker JS shrank roughly 34%
   in compressed size versus the pre-Phase-15 peak (including dropping much of
   <code>opal-parser</code> and trimming corelib/IRB paths from the shipped gem).</p>

